<item>
            <title>[LU-18353] prohibit setting inode limit at Pool Quotas</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18353</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It is impossible to set inode limits for Pool Quotas until MDT Pools would be implemented.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;lctl pool_list dltawork
Pools from dltawork:
dltawork.ddn_hdd
dltawork.ddn_ssd
dltawork.ddn_sas_ssd

lfs setquota -p 101 --pool ddn_ssd -b 10G -B 11G -i 0 -I 0 /lustre/exafs/client/testfs/
lfs setquota: Cannot find pool &apos;ddn_ssd&apos;
lfs setquota: quotactl failed: No such file or directory
setquota failed: No such file or directory &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need to add a check in utils:set_quota to return an error and print a warning if someone tries to set inode limit for quota pool to avoid confusing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
